    public class IfxSqli
extends java.lang.Object
implements IfxProtocol
    The IfxSqli class implements IfxProtocol according to SQLI specification.

      • getaRow

        public boolean getaRow(int direction,
              int count,
              int scrolltype,
              int isscrollcurs,
              java.sql.Statement stmt)
                throws java.sql.SQLException
        get the requested row. if the requested row is not in the tuple buffer then fetch it from the server support for scrollable cursors.
        Specified by:
        getaRow in interface IfxProtocol
        Parameters:
        direction - Valid values are FETCH_FORWARD/FETCH_REVERSE.
        count - number of rows to move forward/backward. or desired row (DIR_ABSL) note: if FETCH_REVERSE then count==1.
        scrolltype - either absolute, relative, next, ... etc.
        isscrollcurs - - is it a scroll cursor ?
        stmt - - used eventually to see if the user is changing the return type of the data. See executeScrollFetch().
        Returns:
        true if a valid row is found, false otherwise.
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException

      • executeScrollFetch

        public void executeScrollFetch(int scrolltype,
                      int index,
                      java.sql.Statement stmt,
                      int fetchBufferSize)
                        throws java.sql.SQLException
        executeScrollFetch() calls sendScrollFetch() to seen the Scroll cursor SQ_SFETCH message to the server. Then calls receivemessage() to get the result back.

        scrolltype - Type of scroll behavior (absolute, relative etc).
        index - Index into row.
        fetchBufferSize - , 0 or user requested size
        Throws:
        java.sql.SQLException - if database access error occurs.
